1256 to track the options which have not been set (so the default values can be used). Without this map
1257 there would be no list of all the config file options. ---*/

1262 class of COptionBase that turns the string into a value) ---*/

1266
1267 // All of the addXxxOptions take in the name of the option, and a reference to the field of that option
1268 // in the option structure. Depending on the specific type, it may take in a default value, and may
1269 // take in extra options. The addXxxOptions mostly follow the same pattern, so please see addDoubleOption
1270 // for detailed comments.
1271 //
1272 // List options are those that can be an unknown number of elements, and also take in a reference to
1273 // an integer. This integer will be populated with the number of elements of that type unmarshaled.
1274 //
1275 // Array options are those with a fixed number of elements.
1276 //
1277 // List and Array options should also be able to be specified with the string "NONE" indicating that there
1278 // are no elements. This allows the option to be present in a config file but left blank.
1279
1280 /*!< \brief addDoubleOption creates a config file parser for an option with the given name whose
1281 value can be represented by a su2double.*/
1282
1283 void addDoubleOption(const string& name, su2double & option_field, su2double default_value);
1284
1285 void addStringOption(const string& name, string & option_field, string default_value);
1286
1287 void addIntegerOption(const string& name, int & option_field, int default_value);
1288
1289 void addUnsignedLongOption(const string& name, unsigned long & option_field, unsigned long default_value);
1290
1291 void addUnsignedShortOption(const string& name, unsigned short & option_field, unsigned short default_value);
1292
1293 void addLongOption(const string& name, long & option_field, long default_value);
1294
1295 void addBoolOption(const string& name, bool & option_field, bool default_value);
1296
1297 // enum types work differently than all of the others because there are a small number of valid
1298 // string entries for the type. One must also provide a list of all the valid strings of that type.
1299 template <class Tenum, class Tfield>
1300 void addEnumOption(const string name, Tfield& option_field, const map<string,Tenum>& enum_map, Tenum default_value);
1301

1482 /*!
1483 * \brief Get reference origin for moment computation.
1484 * \param[in] val_marker - the marker we are monitoring.
1485 * \return Reference origin (in cartesians coordinates) for moment computation.
1486 */
1487 std::array<su2double,3> GetRefOriginMoment(unsigned short val_marker) const {
1488 std::array<su2double,3> RefOriginMoment{{0.0}};
1489 if(val_marker < nMarker_Monitoring) {
1490 RefOriginMoment[0] = RefOriginMoment_X[val_marker];
1491 RefOriginMoment[1] = RefOriginMoment_Y[val_marker];
1492 RefOriginMoment[2] = RefOriginMoment_Z[val_marker];
1493 }
1494 return RefOriginMoment;
1495 }
1496

2913 if (!nDV_Value) return 0;
2914 unsigned short sum = 0;
2915 for (unsigned short iDV = 0; iDV < nDV; iDV++) {
2916 sum += nDV_Value[iDV];
2917 }
2918 return sum;
2919 }

3347 * \param[in] val_tag - Value of the tag in which we are interested.
3348 * \return Value of the marker <i>val_marker</i> that is in the geometry file
3349 * for the surface that has the tag.

3352 for (unsigned short iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker_All; iMarker++) {
3353 if (val_tag == Marker_All_TagBound[iMarker]) return iMarker;
3354 }
3355 return -1;
3356 }

3745 /*!
3746 * \brief Return true if a fluid solver is in use.
3747 */
3748 bool GetFluidProblem(void) const {
3749 switch (Kind_Solver) {
3750 case MAIN_SOLVER::EULER : case MAIN_SOLVER::NAVIER_STOKES: case MAIN_SOLVER::RANS:
3751 case MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER : case MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES: case MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS:
3752 case MAIN_SOLVER::NEMO_EULER : case MAIN_SOLVER::NEMO_NAVIER_STOKES:
3753 case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_EULER: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_NAVIER_STOKES: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_RANS:
3754 case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_EULER: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_NAVIER_STOKES: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_RANS:
3755 return true;
3756 default:
3757 return false;
3758 }
3759 }
3760
3761 /*!
3762 * \brief Return true if a structural solver is in use.
3763 */
3764 bool GetStructuralProblem(void) const {
3765 return (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_ELASTICITY) || (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM);
3766 }
3767
3768 /*!
3769 * \brief Return true if a heat solver is in use.
3770 */
3771 bool GetHeatProblem(void) const {
3772 return (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::HEAT_EQUATION) || (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_HEAT);
3773 }
3774
3775 /*!
3776 * \brief Return true if a high order FEM solver is in use.
3777 */
3778 bool GetFEMSolver(void) const {
3779 switch (Kind_Solver) {
3780 case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_EULER: case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_NAVIER_STOKES: case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_RANS: case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_LES:
3781 case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM_EULER: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM_NS: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM_RANS:
3782 return true;
3783 default:
3784 return false;
3785 }
3786 }
3787
3788 /*!
3789 * \brief Return true if a NEMO solver is in use.
3790 */
3791 bool GetNEMOProblem(void) const {
3792 switch (Kind_Solver) {
3793 case MAIN_SOLVER::NEMO_EULER : case MAIN_SOLVER::NEMO_NAVIER_STOKES:
3794 return true;
3795 default:
3796 return false;
3797 }
3798 }
3799
3800 /*!
3801 * \brief Return true if an AUSM method is in use.
3802 */
3803 bool GetAUSMMethod(void) const {
3804 switch (Kind_Upwind_Flow) {
3805 case UPWIND::AUSM : case UPWIND::AUSMPLUSUP: case UPWIND::AUSMPLUSUP2: case UPWIND::AUSMPLUSM:
3806 return true;
3807 default:
3808 return false;
3809 }
3810 }

6199 /*!
6200 * \brief Set the position of the center of the volumetric heat source.
6201 * \param[in] x_cent = X position of the center of the volumetric heat source.
6202 * \param[in] y_cent = Y position of the center of the volumetric heat source.
6203 * \param[in] z_cent = Z position of the center of the volumetric heat source.
6204 */
6205 inline void SetHeatSource_Center(su2double x_cent, su2double y_cent, su2double z_cent) {

6207 }
